FBIS4-43407 "drweu116_o_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-116 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 CYPRUS Notes Support for Sanctions Notes Support for Sanctions NC1506123094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 1030 GMT 15 Jun 94 NC1506123094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] Asked to comment on a REUTER report last night that the governments of European Union states may ask the Twelve to take action if they believe the Turkish side is continuing to obstruct progress in the confidence-building measures, government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis said the Cypriot Government thinks that sanctions are one way to end the Turkish side's intransigence. Referring to the sanctions, the government spokesman said the most important measure is an embargo against the pseudostate's illegal exports, an issue on which a European Court decision is still pending.
